value.0: What do you want?
No, and you're giving me enough to do just by talking to me. Now go away.

Pfah! You mean Agnar Magnus. He's an upstart and a thug in the pay of the Luskans. His family stole the throne and massacred His Lordship's ancestors, let the Amians and Illuskans come in and take all our wood and iron, then practically handed the Jarldom over to Luskan. But a revolt by the nobles and peasants put -that- wrong to right.
You'd be a fool to say something like that around here, if you know what's good for you.
Don't you damn well forget it. There are Luskan spies and traitors under every other rock. And with all the questions you're asking, I'm beginning to think you might be one of them....
What do you think I am, His Lordship's social secretary? Not a chance. He's got better things to do that meet with nosy strangers.
The Mountain Road, which takes you down to the Crossroads and from there to the rest of Ostland.
Well, there're the mines up in the High Pass, I guess - that's north off the Mountain road - but they're pretty much closed down, now that there's no more iron left.
You can thank that ancient bastard Pimpant Magnus and his son Heinrich for that. They sold all our iron to Amia and Luskan before the war. Good thing we got rid of 'em.
The town of Huyslod, up in the mountains. The First Axe Thorden Lithyl holds his court there.
How the hells do I know? Do I look like the First Axe to you? Do you have any other stupid questions?
This is the fortress of Ostdur, capital of Ostland and seat of His Lordship the Axe Raorik Bathrie.
That's all, thanks.
Is there any work to be had around here?
Thanks for all your help.
I have a couple of other questions....
Who's this Magnus guy I keep hearing about?
So the Magnus clan aren't the rightful rulers of Ostland?
Thanks for the lesson in local politics.
I have a few other questions, if you don't mind?
But Agnar Magnus wasn't responsible himself, right? This all happened a long time ago?
You guys keep things on a pretty tight leash around here.
Gotcha. I'll just be on my way now....
Nope, not me! But I do have some other questions I was hoping you could help me out with.
Can I make an appointment to see the Axe?
Gotcha. I'll just be on my way now....
I see. Perhaps you could answer a few other questions I have?
What lies to the east of here?
Anything else?
No iron? I've heard they were all played out. How did that happen?
Thanks for the information. You've been very helpful.
I have a few more questions, if you don't mind.
What lies to the west of here?
Why so far from the action?
Er... No. I think I'll be on my way now.
Um... I do, actually...
I was hoping you could tell me a bit about this town.
I see. Thanks for your time. Bye, now.
I see. Perhaps you could answer a few other questions I have?
